'''Level 948''' is the 949<sup>th</sup> level of the Backrooms. It is seemingly infinite, and it contains a useful and unique object.

== Description ==
'''Level 948''', commonly known as "Road Convenience", is an area that represents an underground tunnel that serves as a passageway to cross a road. This level is notable for its presence of '''Object 16'''.
=== General Information ===
{{Blurimage|file=Undergroundtunnel.jpg|caption=<span style="color:white">The first known photo of '''Level 948'''.</span>|align=right}}
'''Level 948''' is a modern subterranean tunnel composed of white concrete and brick walls as its main building material. Navigation is made difficult by the level's confusing turns and dead ends. In response, explorers use spray paint to graffiti symbols on the walls to mark their whereabouts, making it easier to navigate. Common sights in this level are traffic cones, bicycles, and exit signs, as well as arrows on the walls, which typically lead to dead ends. Some machinery noises are also heard faintly within the area.
{{Blurimage|file=Underpasswithsign.jpeg|caption=<span style="color:white">A junction between the tunnels. Note that the exit sign does not lead to the exit.</span>|align=right}}
Junctions between the tunnels commonly appear, allowing one to enter a new tunnel. In these junctions, rectangular lights line the brick walls, illuminating the area. Exit signs create an illusion of leaving the tunnel, but typically there is no relation between the path of the exit signs and legitimate exits. Going deeper into the junctions may lead one to a staircase, which allows one to exit the level. The machinery sounds heard in the tunnels can be traced to large machines within the junctions, responsible for powering the level. Cardboard boxes can be seen lying on the ground everywhere, which rarely contain [[Object 1|Almond Water]] cans and food packages, though they are generally empty.

Yellow and black tapes can be seen wrapping around the dark, narrow and dusty areas of the level, where '''Object 16''' is harvested. Since the walls and floors are made of undried '''Object 16''', it is very difficult to traverse them. The undried '''Object 16''' floors take on similar properties to quicksand, and as a result, escape is nearly impossible for sunken wanderers. To combat this, [[M.E.G.]] operatives have located all '''Object 16''' pitfalls and put up "DO NOT CROSS" tape to ensure people's safety.

Rarely, one can find empty storefronts in '''Level 948''', resembling a vacant space in a shopping mall. The rows of shelves are mostly empty, but sometimes include cans of [[Object 1|Almond Water]] or firearms. When a can of [[Object 1|Almond Water]] is taken away for a few hours, another can of [[Object 1|Almond Water]] appears at the same place. There are LED advertisements and posters on the walls promoting shows, products, or even other levels. These areas are chosen as living quarters by inhabitants because of the shelter they provide, the constant supply of [[Object 1|Almond Water]], the accessibility of food and the wood and metal shelves that can be broken down to make tools. In addition, the concentration of '''Object 16''' is higher near these structures.

In '''Level 948''', the ceilings are in poor condition due to the lack of structural support, and the least structurally-sound ceilings collapse randomly. Consequently, in '''Level 948''', the most casualties are caused by collapsing roofs. Mold or water leakage are both signs of a hazardous ceiling. When a ceiling collapses, the rubble formed completely blocks the narrow crawlspaces, making it impossible to advance through the tunnel.

=== Skirodemium ===
<div class="meg-fandom-logoblock"><div style="color: black">
<center>'''Report on new object'''</center>
<span style="color: black">In '''Level 948''', I've discovered a special kind of concrete. The concrete looks like normal concrete, but it can withstand a lot of weight and temperature! Perhaps we can collect them to make durable buildings and structures? It is also very common, we should be able to gather them cheaply and sell them to colonies!<div style="text-align:right">By Researcher ███</div></span></div></div>

'''"Skirodemium"''', named after the Greek word of '''"σκυρόδεμα"''', meaning "concrete", is an exclusive object found in '''Level 948'''. It takes on the appearance of concrete, but the main difference lies in its unique applications, determined by what substances it is paired with. It can be found everywhere in walls as impure '''Skirodemium''', but there is a higher concentration nearby the empty storefronts mentioned above.{{Blurimage|file=Skirodemium.jpeg|caption=<span style="color:white">A brick of Skirodemium.</span>|align=right}}

Since '''Level 948''' is the only source of '''Skirodemium''', many colonies visit the level to gather a large amount of it to use it as a building material for their bases. This includes the [[M.E.G.]], which has a colony in '''Level 948''' to gather and sell '''Skirodemium''' to other colonies or outposts.

According to the experiments performed by the [[M.E.G.]], 100 cm³ of '''Skirodemium''' can withstand more than 3000 psi of pressure and a large temperature. It is a very good insulator as well, and 1 m³ of '''Skirodemium''' only weighs about 1kg. It is very durable due to being able to maintain over 99.99% of its original resistance in multiple resistance tests. It can resist dynamite explosions and multiple shots of 500 S&W bullets. As a result, it has a lot of applications, such as making heavy machines that need to endure high pressures and temperatures. Some colonies in several levels use it as their main building material as it is a cheap replacement for concrete.

Blending '''Skirodemium''' with a certain amount of particular liquids produces new materials, but it is unfortunately impossible to revert it back to its original form after this process. For example, adding 1 drop of Cashew Water can turn '''Skirodemium''' into a soft plastic, which can be used to make bottles. The following is a list of compounds that can be produced by '''Skirodemium''' and their ingredients:

