'''Skirodemium''' quickly became a highly sought after item following its discovery. The [[M.E.G.]] has created a monopoly around '''Object 16''', selling it to colonies and outposts in different levels. As a result, '''Skirodemium''' has ended up as one of the most commercialized items distributed throughout the Backrooms.

== Entities ==
[[Entity 3|Smilers]] and [[Entity 10|Skin-Stealers]] are known to be found in '''Level 948'''. The entities always appear in hordes and rush the person they see at first glance. There is also a unique entity.

{{Entity Class|no=N/A|Hab=Only Level 948|Agg=1|Int=2|Dan=4}}
{{Blurimage|file=Trashcans.webp|caption=A picture of two green '''Trash Cans'''. Their wheels are hidden.|align=right}}
'''Trash Cans''' are unique entities which only inhabit in '''Level 948'''. They resemble ordinary gray trash bins with wheels seen in [[The Frontrooms]], hence their name. While a mix of standard trash cans and their entity counterparts can be found in '''Level 948''', the particularly dull '''Skirodemium''' composition of '''Trash Cans''' makes it simple to distinguish between the two. Specifically, the '''Skirodemium''' used is in plastic form, which is sometimes painted green, blue, or rarely red.

'''Trash Cans''' act as barricades in dark, narrow hallways, only letting wanderers pass when they deposit their personal trash into the bin. When wanderers comply, '''Trash Cans''' will be pacified toward that person unless attacked. Upon refusal, they will become aggressive and chase the wanderer down and swallow them. If wanderers don't have any trash, they require wanderers to give away any survival resources, like [[Object 1|Almond Water]].

When '''Trash Cans''' are provoked by a wanderer, their wheels allow them to pursue wanderers at high speeds (~15mph). In addition, they attack wanderers in groups so it is harder for people to deal with them. When they catch a victim, they swallow them and digest them using pure hydrochloric acid. However, they are not resilient to physical damage.

