Due to the nature of this level, many colonies and outposts have been settled. Two of them managed to be the most influential among all of them.
=== M.E.G. 948 Researchers ===
This group was established by the [[M.E.G.]] after the discovery of '''Object 16'''. There are 10 members and their objective is to explore '''Level 948''' and collect '''Object 16'''. They give out free [[Object 1|Almond Water]] to lost wanderers and help them to adapt to the environment. Everyday, they excavate Skiromedium from the storefronts and sell it to colonies from different levels. The '''R.O.U.''' is their primary customer, purchasing large quantities of '''Skirodemium''' to build new structures.
=== Republic of Underpassia (R.O.U.) ===
'''Republic of Underpassia''', informally called '''Passia''', is a self-declared colony which was founded a week after this level's discovery. It consists of 135 wanderers who have decided to settle in '''Level 948'''. They are moderately armed and actively killing dangerous entities. They own 1km² of land and the border is marked using plastic barricades, preventing other wanderers from infiltrating. A store is set up outside the border, letting other wanderers to buy [[Object 1|Almond Water]] and [[Object 6|Moth Jelly]].}}}}}}</div>
== Entrances and Exits ==
=== Entrances ===
*Entering any underpass that looks out of place in any level leads here.
=== Exits ===
*Noclipping into an air vent leads to [[Level 34]].
*Noclipping into the pipes on the ceiling leads to [[Level 2]].
*Exiting by walking up a staircase can lead to a random outdoor level.
*Walking for a week non-stop while not following any exit signs will cause the level to fade into [[Special:RandomInCategory/Levels|a random level]].
*Following an exit sign written "YELLOW" leads one to [[Level 0]].
*Following an exit sign written "HUB" leads one to [[The Hub]].
*Following an exit sign written "STATION154" leads one to [[Level 154]].
*Following an exit sign written "BRIGHTENESS" leads one to [[Level 228]].

